heat/engine/resources/openstack/glance/i.message:
Do you suggest creating a new class, and make it parent for all resources that have caching? So they will have multiple parent classes?
I do not think it will simplify anything...

Code reduction I can think of is something like this:
We put clear_cache_method in Resource class.
It will receive varying amount of args and named arg which will be object of function we need to clear cache from.
Something like that:
def clear_cache_from_function(self, func, *args):
    func(None, *args)

(Why I puy None as first argument - actually first argument is ignored as it is usually self, when cached function is called).

And then we can call this method from resources:
def handle_delete(self):
  ...
  func_to_clear_cache = self.client_plugin()._find_image_id
  for name_or_id in (self.properties[self.NAME], self.resource_id):
    self.clear_cache_from_function(func_to_clear_cache, self.client_plugin().context.tenant_id, name_or_id)

Or I can simplify even more. Base method in Resource will be:
def clear_cache_from_function(self, func):
  for name_or_id in (self.properties[self.NAME], self.resource_id):
    func(None, self.client_plugin().context.tenant_id), name_or_id)

With such implementation we will call this method in glance image like that:
def handle_delete(self):
  ...
  func_to_clear_cache = self.client_plugin()._find_image_id
  self.clear_cache_from_function(func_to_clear_cache)

And in Neutron base resource we override base resource method, because there are also other arguments.

I think second way is better. I'll change the patch accordingly and you will look at result.

you could escape from override handle_delete, if move calling clear_cache_from_function to default implementation and create resource attribute like "cached_functions", where will add cached functions, so clear_cache_from_function will be look like:

def clear_cache_from_function(self):
    if cfg.CONF.cache.enabled:
        for func in self.cached_functions:
            for name_or_id in (self.properties[self.NAME], self.resource_id):
                func.invalidate(None, self.client_plugin().context.tenant_id,
                                name_or_id)

