nova/tests/functional/libvirt/test_repor.message:
It is. With the previous code, mypy couldn't detect that 'supports_amd_sev would always return a boolean since it was coupled to the 'self._supports_amd_sev' attribute and that was only set by side-effect in '_set_amd_sev_support'. Another example:

  import typing as ty

  class Foo:
      def __init__(self):
          self._bar: ty.Optional[bool] = None

      def get_bar() -> bool:
          if self._bar is None:
              self._set_bar()
          return self._bar

      def _set_bar() -> None:
          self._bar = True

That'll fail because the type of 'self._bar' is one of True, False or None, but we've said it can only be True or False. I could rework this to add a totally unnecessary 'is not None' check, but I think what I did instead was better. Basically the equivalent of:

  class Foo:
      def __init__(self):
          self._bar: ty.Optional[bool] = None

      def get_bar() -> bool:
          if self._bar is not None:
              self._bar = True
          return self._bar

